</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unicophorus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nicophorus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://homepages.go.com/~aela_eq/Shield.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Less Talk, More Fight </span><br>  Posts: 844<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/4/01 8:08:30 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://homepages.go.com/~aela_eq/Shield.gif border=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmm FG큦 :)</span><hr size=1> You know.. the thing is, its not like Ragefire spawns are being wasted...<br>
<br>
If that were the case, or hell if Ragefire was actually up more than two minutes after spawning, the folks arguing FG reservations being a restriction on a bottleneck would have a point.<br>
<br>
But, he's not... and so they don't.<br>
<br>
Now read over Krungles last post and think carefully.  Don't think about those darned low levels doing a three hour fire giant raid (those greedy bastards, three hours and then just leaving the place... all while Ragefire wasn't even up, what the hell were they thinking)... no, think about the other part...<br>
<br>
The monk who'd been feigning there for 18 hours.  The Paladin trying for a spot on the Ragefire camp.  The mage following us in for a spot in the Ragefire line.  The guild of higherlevel folks led by one of the more respected Paladins on the server following our raid a few hours later (hint, he posted just before me).  That's at least four clerics (or more) represented waiting for one spawn that did, or did not happen.<br>
<br>
That's not counting the tells I received pre-raid asking if we were going in for Ragefire (we weren't, aren't, and won't do it).  All told, I ran a greedy raid over a three hour window for a group of level 40's during a time when Ragefire wasn't up, while AT LEAST four people were already in line for Ragefire.<br>
<br>
Now think, just for a moment...<br>
<br>
Even if Fire Giants were out of the equation, would that have changed the situation?  Answe: NO.  Remember, that monk was there for 18 hours.  Eighteen hours... That's at least two full fire giant respawns (which btw, weren't reserved and probably did not get used) while he was waiting on Ragefire...<br>
<br>
I know its very easy to think that if Fire Giants were just removed from the reservation then somehow YOU would be at the front of the line.  I know its easy to assume that its just those damned greedy people reserving Fire Giants keeping YOU from your hard earned epic.<br>
<br>
However, facts don't weigh that out.<br>
<br>
I've ran four Fire Giant raids recently.  One was walked on.  Not a single one of those raids saw a Ragefire spawn (including the people that walked over our raid, they didn't get a Rage spawn either).  So, exactly how many high level clerics has my reservations kept from attaining their epic.<br>
<br>
Answer: ZERO<br>
<br>
That's right, zero.  Not a single one.  Why? Well... Ragefire wasn't up.  No Ragefire, no Cleric Epic.  No Ragefire, no one was harmed in that raid.  OTOH, I've actually taken a lot of people that have never raided, ran them through some very enjoyable raids, gained an item or two for some of them, and taught them a lot about what an organized raid SHOULD be like.  Given that the entire server isn't level 55+, I'd say I've actually done something for the server.  Given that I've not made a single item, nor pp, nor much xp on these raids, I'd venture that my own personal gains have not been the reason I've done them.  Certain martyr wannabe's can count that as their suck commentary.<br>
<br>
So, I'm asking.  How would removing Fire Giant reservations change things one iota?  That monk will still be there 18 hours.  THose forty five Cleric alts in SolB will still be there.  Ragefire is the bottleneck, NOT the fire giants.  At worst the few folks reserving FG's like Watchers did (and Europa Tribes has done) will only have a small chance of their raid actually GETTING either Ragefire or even the right to camp ragefire since in all likelihood Ragefire will ALREADY be camped on their arrival.<br>
<br>
As indicated, I've run four Fire Giant raids in the last two months.  The longest (the first) ran 3.5 hours, the shortest (the last) ran 2 hours.  All told I've 'abused' 11 hours of Sol B in eight weeks without a single Ragefire spawn.  I'd be impressed if someone could actually demonstrate how that is greedy.  Honestly demonstrate it please?<br>
<br>
You can't.  Yet, here I am in this thread being referred to right and left as the greedy one... I just don't facking get it.  I'm one of the few people NOT abusing the reservation system (or at least having to use the reservation system in a way they don't want to).  I've made it clear in every raid I've run that if Rage is up, we're not going to be involved, we'll leave him quietly in place... so... no clerics were affected (or effected depending on which version of Verant speak you like).  Also, in every one of our raids the LIST for Ragefire squatting rights was already two or more deep WHEN WE STARTED.<br>
<br>
In short, abolohing FG reservations will only harm people wanting to use FG's the right way.  It won't get you your Ragefire any faster Europa Tribes, Watchers, or anyone else involved here... only Ragefire deciding to spawn will get that.. and only if you're not held up by that monk who's been there for three days...<br>
<br>
It's time people realized that Fire Giants have just been a scapegoat of the real problem, one spawn bottlenecks.  Removing them from the equation isn't going to effect the equation one iota... because FG's aren't what's stopping you from getting your epic... that 40 person line is going to stop it... and remember, an honest Fire Giant raid actually respects that 40 person line.<br>
<br>
So please, honestly find greed there.  There is only greed on one side of this problem right now... and it isn't on the side of the FG raiders... and its not universal to the people wanting their cleric epics.  There's a lot of misinformation and doublethink right now on this subject... more people posting their rage at not having their epic would be better served actually thinking the process through.<br>
