<br>
We are on a server that is more or less on a FCFS server and is by no means a helpful or great server other than that. What this meant 6 months ago was that if I was in a location first and claimed the spawn it was accepted as being valid. Today that is no longer true. Today FCFS on Brell means that if I have a raid crew at the point of attacking the spawn first before it is engaged then it is mine.<br>
<br>
What does this have to do with FGs and Ragefire? I'll explain that now and thank you for bearing with me. The server has decided that Ragefire is not reservable and that the FG's are. This is a simple fact we have all seen the voting results. FG's can be reserved for any reason what so ever. There are no checks or balances in place as to why you want to reserve them you just can.  In fact you can schedule the FGs and not even take them down. That is also not in the rules. There are many ways in which a person can abuse the system. But I digress from my original thought.<br>
<br>
So a person can by all rights reserve the FGs even though someone may be &quot;camping&quot; ragefire. Ragefire can then spawn but within the time window that you can not take down the FGs. The rules do not state that you can take the FGs down if ragefire is up. It also says you can not take them down if you have a Naggy raid scheduled. FGs have priority over both Ragefire and Naggy. So the camping person can do 1 of 2 things.<br>
1) They can ignore the FG reservation thus hurting the reputation of their guild and themselves for stepping on a FG reservation (the reason for the reservation does not matter).<br>
2) They can live by the reservation that is in place and hope that said raid is not brining along a Ragefire capable crew.<br>
<br>
Why does the camper have to hope that the person is not bringing along a Ragefire capable crew? FCFS rules as they stand on this server. Though I may have been the first person to spot Ragefire up and could have easily had a raid crew there in under 5 minutes I and the guild I belong to followed the second option of respecting the FG reservation.<br>
<br>
Now the reserved FG raid crew goes in to clear the FGs as they had intended and because they reach the lair with a full raid crew before the camping person could they have instant rights over the Ragefire spawn because a camper is not respected but a reservation is.<br>
<br>
So you see the group that scheduled the FGs did nothing wrong they simple followed the rules that were voted on.<br>
<br>
You can laugh off what I am saying or take a strong look at how FGs are being used and either do something about it. To say that allowing FGs to be reserved hurts no one think again. The joy I once had in this game got destroyed in a 22hour camp by which the rules of this board allowed me to be pissed on for lack of a better term.<br>
<br>
I have been very vocal in the past about how FGs should and shouldn't be used. I did not reserve FGs because I felt they should be for those learning FGs, I lvl'd a monk so that I would not interfere in anyones chance at experiencing and having fun in the game. In the end it did not pay off, my personal belief meant nothing and if I do decide to return to this game I once enjoyed and hangout with a guild and group of friends I really liked I will have to sell my beliefs out and start signing up for FG raids.<br>
