1) Puma wouldn't have made the reservation, he'd have just been there camping too... granted, he and Nasrens alt could have shared gem scores or something... both having a raid capable group ready to pop in with five groups in five minutes... its a weekend, its very possible.  Also, it's quite possible that without that reservation, Puma (sorry to pick on him, just continuing the example for continuity) would have logged in 18 hours earlier and been there before Nasren's alt...<br>
<br>
2) or maybe someone else would have (there's one other name referenced here, Quoj...) maybe he'd been there first with a raid capable force.<br>
<br>
3) Maybe two or three of you'd have been there simultaneously... who's to say who's going to respect the others First in FCFS... hypothetically Puma was there First, but Nasren has a raid there first... maybe Quoj is there first, but Thorondar is enraged and (following his quote) &quot;walks all over your Ragefire raid&quot;...<br>
<br>
4) Maybe an entire raid of Watchers would have sat on their asses for the weekend in SolB for that Ragefire spawn... THAT is the only way to have guaranteed Nasren would have his epic... and I can guarantee you you'd all be bored off your ass and pissed about it... THAT is what FCFS guarantees... because when it comes to getting their guild a Cleric epic, people WILL do that... if you dont do it you're just playing odds that aren't in your favor.<br>
<br>
Do you see my point?  FCFS does change how last weekend played out... only one Cleric still gets their epic over that same timetable... maybe the Cleric changes, maybe it doesn't.  The only guaranteed thing is that someone (or sometwo) would still be pissed at how it worked out...  Maybe its some Cleric from the guild { Big doo doo heads } that for some reason had people there and started Ragefire while Watchers groups (on standby admittedly) were porting into Lavastorm (since you've already indicated you weren't standing by IN SolB).  <br>
<br>
Trying to place the blame of this or the solution to this on Fire Giants is misplaced rage.<br>
<br>
Run through what you'd be doing if this were an open FCFS system (Fire Giants, Ragefire).  Multiply that set of strategies by what... 20 to 40 guilds capable of doing the same thing... divide that by one weekend... allowing for three Ragefire spawns thats three new Epic Clerics (CHEER... I DO like seeing Clerics get an epic and agree about its community benefits)... but that's still 17 to 37 pissed off guilds and an equal number of in game conflicts... hell, I can honestly see it boiling down to in game petitions, GM issues, Kill Stealing, and Ninja looting... THAT is what FCFS will do... right now, the barrier has been the Fire Giant reservations, abused or not abused<br>
<br>
Put aside your anger and think this through...<br>
